Do you think? No. The answer is no. Your mind thinks. You have a relationship with your mind. It's the closest relationship you have. If we think we \emph{are} our mind, we ignore the most significant relationship in our lives. The relationship through which we can achieve whatever freedom can be had in this life. Not freedom \emph{of} choice. Freedom \emph{from} choice. Choice is a chore performed by the mind. \emph{Intuition} is a vibration that emanates from the heart. With these chants we \emph{cultivate} intuition so that rather than \emph{choose}, we just \emph{know} what needs to be done.

If she who sings prays twice, let's add movement and make it prayer squared. All praises due to the One who does not exist. The idea of God is of little use to one who sees Wow everywhere. For the rest of us, we install these open source \emph{programs} into the computers known as our minds, and run them in various configurations, learning the correct syntax to thin the fog of spiritual ignorance or at the very least make it glow a little bit so we can remember to enjoy it. So we can remember to rejoice and celebrate the opportunity to be a fool; to have a body; hands; a voice; a friend; a relationship.

What is drone?

How do we sing?

Like in much of yoga we combine, blend and balance \emph{force} and \emph{surrender}.

How is this book organized?

What are the chakras?

Ganesha guardian of the kundalini

these are just notes

writing, the death of spoken word

Taking classes and studying meditation I was always trying to \emph{visualize} the Chakras, visualize myself becoming centered. I realized that centering is this thing that I've been able to do since I was a child. There's some part of me --- maybe it's my awareness --- that's --- I don't know what --- floating in the wind? And I can draw that part of myself into my physical body --- but deeper than any actual part of the body --- into an undefinable center, and become grounded and centered.

And if I do that --- take the time to center myself --- I will be able to manage the emotions that arise throughout the activity and interactivity of the day. If not they are likely to be as storm winds, my consciousness --- my moods --- a ship tossed in the waves. 


